" Background: •	This contract provides a temporary staff augmentation solution to support budget operations, with contractors directly involved in the execution of budget-related tasks. •	They contribute to accurate financial reporting and promote transparency in budget matters. •	They are responsible for preparing and distributing the January 2025 Division Budget Reports, ensuring timely and precise documentation. •	Additionally, the contractor is assisting staff in assessing the reestimate process, helps align the project schedule, and supports the analysis of workbooks, Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), and other related documentation to ensure milestones and deliverables are met. •	The contractors perform stress test analysis on the portfolio, validate portfolio data, and prepare the loss reserve report, ensuring accurate and reliable financial assessments. •	They handle other data calls based on portfolio data, providing the necessary insights and documentation to support decision-making. •	The staff keeps abreast of executive orders and relevant OMB Circulars, including A-11 (which provides guidance on preparing, submitting, and executing the federal budget) and A-129 (which outlines the policies and procedures for managing and accounting for federal credit programs), ensuring all budgetary processes comply with the latest federal guidelines and mandates. •	The staff is knowledgeable of the Federal Credit Reform Act (FCRA) as it relates to the portfolio, ensuring compliance with FCRA provisions for budgeting, accounting, and reporting of federal credit programs."

Through access to AI data preparation tools, capabilities, and services, the DoD will be positioned to effectively prepare AI data to support the full range of AI activities across the DoD.  The scope of this PWS shall encompass all tasks needed to create, acquire, curate, prepare, manage, or secure data sets for use in DoD AI models and application development, testing, certification, and operation.   Examples of such tasks include but are not exclusive to Extract Transform Load (ETL) and Data Engineering Development, Database Design and Development, Data Science Development, Data Analysis, Data collection and curation, and Project and Outreach Program Management. For the execution of DoD Task Orders, these activities shall be performed while maintaining appropriate security and ethical considerations, including Federal and DoD regulations governing cyber security, information security, operational security, ethical standards of conduct, conflicts of interest, and AI Ethical Principles.

The contractor shall assess and evaluate existing NASA Science Mission Directorate (SMD) programming and procedures to identify gaps and/or underlying issues in support of the open science strategic initiatives. Recommend updates to strategy documents and collect modifications for input. Provide an assessment and recommendations to cross-cutting alignments across the Directorate. The contractor shall facilitate planning and discussion meetings to conduct strategic assessment activities, provide recommendations on agenda and materials and document results, and report findings and recommendations to the OSCDO and other leadership to inform mission directorate processes. The contractor shall develop and foster relationships with Agency points of contact and others to further the OSCDO offices’ goals. The contractor shall monitor developments in and around open science and technology polices relative to Agency and OCSDO goals and directives. The contractor shall provide management and assessment of OCSDO schedules, milestones, actions, and risks using applicable tools and trackers. The contractor shall review and assess strategic engagement opportunities on behalf of SMD OCSDO Front Office, Open Science Data Officer, and Open Science Program Scientist and recommend strategies to maximize reach and impact.
